Dangote Fertiliser has promised to train farmers in the South-East on better ways to obtain bumper yields. A representative of the company, Ekene Obiefuna, in his presentation at the 2021 Enugu International Trade Fair, said with the training on the best ways to apply fertiliser, farming would become very lucrative and attract more people. He explained that the fertiliser company, which has commenced operations, had the capacity to meet and exceed the domestic demand for the commodity across the country. President of the Enugu Chamber of Commerce, Industry, Mines, and Agriculture (ECCIMA), Mr Emeka Nwandu, said the entrepreneur had, through his company, Dangote Group, added a lot of value to the countryâ€™s economy, operating in almost every sector. 